Package org.javafp.parsecj

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ConsumedT<S,A>
    ConsumedT is a discriminated union between a Consumed type and an Empty type.
    Message<S>
    An message which represents a (potential) parse failure.
    Parser<S,A>
    A parser is essentially a function taking the input stream and returning a ConsumedT.
    State<S>
    An interface for parseable, immutable symbol streams.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Combinators
    A collection of parser combinator functions.
    Merge
    Utility function for merging parse messages.
    Parser.Ref<S,A>
    A lazily initialised reference to a Parser.
    Reply<S,A>
    A Parser result, essentially a discriminated union between a Success and an Error.
    Reply.Error<S,A>
    An unsuccessful parse result.
    Reply.Ok<S,A>
    A successful parse result.
    Text
    Parser combinators to be used with Character streams.
